               <div class="btArticleContent ">
               <div class="bodytext contentText"> <p>To keep the&nbsp;members of your household comfortable throughout the year, you may rely quite a&nbsp;bit on your heating and cooling system. Naturally, keeping your household safe&nbsp;is even more important than creating a temperate environment. If you exercise&nbsp;caution and implement a few safety measures, you should be able to accomplish both objectives all year long.</p> </div>
               <div class="bodytext contentText"> <p>&nbsp;</p><p>At East Side&nbsp;Ventilation, we understand the necessity of <a href="/" data-track-event="click" data-track-action="internal_link_clicked">equipping your home</a> with the right&nbsp;HVAC products. Do not hesitate to consult us if you need to install or replace&nbsp;your heating and cooling system. We can also assist you in keeping your&nbsp;equipment in the best condition possible, so you can avoid unfortunate mishaps.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style="font-weight: bold;">How to Create a Safe and Temperate Home Environment </span><br><br>You might not be aware that some habits could easily lead to disaster in the home. Follow these safety tips to ensure the well-being of your household: <br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">· Use the Right Equipment – </span>Never utilize appliances to heat or cool your home if they were not designed to do these things. Do not use your oven to heat your indoor environment, for example. This could easily lead to an injury or fire, especially if you have children or pets in the home.<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">· Schedule Maintenance Visits – </span>By scheduling <a href="//<?php echo $_SERVER['SERVER_NAME']; ?>/furnace-cleaning-winnipeg" data-track-event="click" data-track-action="internal_link_clicked">regular service calls</a>, you can keep your HVAC equipment in top shape. This will help to prevent system failure at the times when you most need your heating and cooling units to work. If you do not have heat in the very cold months or cool air in the hottest months, someone in your household could become ill. <br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">· Safety Equipment – </span>You should always have access to safety equipment in your home. Make sure that you have a carbon monoxide detector, a smoke detector, and a fire extinguisher. If you have a large home or your home consists of multiple levels, you should have more than one of each of these items. Make sure that you replace the batteries in such products regularly, as well.<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">· Plugs and Outlets – </span>Never try to alter the condition of a plug, and do not try to force a plug into an outlet. If a particular plug will not fit in an outlet, either get a new plug, or install a different type of outlet to meet your needs. <br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">· Change Filters –</span> All filters should be replaced periodically. In addition to being less energy efficient than a clean filter, a clogged filter can cause a unit to overheat, which could result in a fire. Your local HVAC professional can change your filters during regular service visits. <br><br>Your heating and cooling system is a crucial aspect of your home. By keeping this equipment ingood shape, you can make sure that your family stays comfortable during every season. Most importantly, routine <a href="//<?php echo $_SERVER['SERVER_NAME']; ?>/aircondition-experts-winnipeg" data-track-event="click" data-track-action="internal_link_clicked">inspection and maintenance</a> can help to keep your household safe. <br><br>Get in touch with East Side Ventilation at <a data-global="phone" href="tel:204-667-8700" data-track-event="click" data-track-action="phone_link">204-667-8700</a>. We provide HVAC repair, maintenance, and installation services in the Winnipeg area. Also, feel free to fill out our <a href="/winnipeg-hvac-company-contact" data-track-event="click" data-track-action="internal_link_clicked">online contact form</a> for assistance.</p> </div>
